Police are searching for two "armed thieves" after a video emerged of a 52-year-old man allegedly being robbed of his Rolex watch in Boksburg on September 25 2019. The suspects allegedly entered a McDonald's restaurant where the man was seated, threatened him with a knife and relieved him of the R50,000 watch. He sustained a minor neck injury. A case of robbery with a weapon other than a gun has been opened.